org.linqs.psl.application.groundrulestore

Interface GroundRuleStore

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    Reasoner
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ADMMReasoner, BooleanMaxWalkSat, BooleanMCSat, ExecutableReasoner, LatentTopicNetworkADMMReasoner, MemoryGroundKernelStore

    public interface GroundRuleStore
    Container for a set of GroundRules.

    Since this container uses set semantics, no two GroundRules that are equal can be stored in it. If a Rule wants to add another GroundRule that does the same thing over the same GroundAtoms, then it should retrieve the original GroundRule, modify it, and call changedGroundRule(GroundRule).

      • changedGroundKernelWeight

        void changedGroundKernelWeight(WeightedGroundRule gk)
        Notifies this store that a WeightedGroundRule's weight was changed.

        This method should be called whenever the weight of a GroundCompatibilityKernel in this store is changed, or the weight of its parent WeightedRule is changed (and the GroundCompatibilityKernel's weight is still tied to it).

        It is not necessary to also call changedGroundRule(GroundRule) if only the weight was changed.

        Parameters:
        gk - the ground kernel with a changed weight

      • changedGroundKernelWeights
